  <section class="my-36">
    <div class="container grid grid-cols-1 gap-12 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="flex flex-col items-start gap-4">
        <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="space-content accordion-section">
        <Accordion>
          <AccordionItem name="exclusive" title="What is systemisation and do I need it?" open>
            <p>
              Systemisation is simply creating a system. In relation to your business, it's about creating systems to
              streamline your operations, improve efficiency and ultimately save you time & effort (and money!). It
              involves looking at what you do and how you do it, documenting existing processes, standardising tasks and
              identifying where you can either automate, outsource, or in some cases actually stop doing a task if it's
              not adding value. It may involve introducing new software or tools, and if we're working together it will
              always involve centering you and how you like to work.
            </p>
          </AccordionItem>
          <AccordionItem name="exclusive" title="What is automation? Is that like AI?">
            <p>
              Automation, in the context I'm using it, means taking something that you or your team currently do
              manually, and making it happen automatically.
            </p>
            <p>
              To achieve this automation, we create rules that tell a piece of software, 'when this happens, do that',
              e.g. 'when a form is submitted, send an email'. There are many ways to implement automations, including
              advanced automations using APIs, webhooks and scripting. In most cases, I'll use 'no-code' or 'low-code'
              tools which are easier for you to maintain on an ongoing basis.
            </p>
          </AccordionItem>
          <AccordionItem name="exclusive" title="How much do systemisation and automation services cost?">
            <p>
              The cost of streamlining your business operations varies depending on the size and complexity of your
              business, your goals, and where you're at right now.
            </p>
            <p>
              I offer a range of services to meet you where you are right now. From ad hoc VA (virtual assistant)
              support to systems audit and CRM implementation and everything in between. My services start at $295 AUD.
            </p>
          </AccordionItem>
          <AccordionItem name="exclusive" title="What is a sufficient color contrast ratio?">
            <p>
              According to WCAG 2.2 AA standards, text should have a minimum contrast ratio of 4.5:1 against its
              background for regular text, and 3:1 for large text (18pt or 14pt bold). For non-text elements like icons
              or buttons, a minimum ratio of 3:1 is required. This ensures content is readable for users with visual
              impairments or color blindness.
            </p>
          </AccordionItem>
          <AccordionItem name="exclusive" title="How do I make custom components accessible?">
            <p>
              To make custom components accessible, focus on these key aspects: use semantic HTML where possible,
              implement proper keyboard support, add appropriate ARIA attributes, manage focus when needed, and ensure
              adequate color contrast. Always test with screen readers and keyboard navigation. Consider using
              established design patterns from the <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/"
                >ARIA Authoring Practices Guide</a
              >.
            </p>
          </AccordionItem>
        </Accordion>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="my-36">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="mb-16">Kind words from clients</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-12 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <Testimonial name="Nadine Brown" title="Floral designer, educator + mentor | The Ivy Institute">
          <p>
            “I can’t tell you how wonderful it is to have someone not only genuinely lovely & honest but who is just so
            super efficient, skilled & forward thinking as Lauren.
          </p>
          <p>
            From web design to launches, resource and course creation to general admin, client communication and beyond,
            Lauren handles many facets of my business now. I feel incredibly supported by Lauren, she just gets it!”
          </p>
        </Testimonial>
        <Testimonial name="Honey Atkinson" title="Photographer + film maker">
          <p>Good stuff.</p>
        </Testimonial>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
